    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fad22bf5_ee898f8b",
        "filename": "golden/go/serialize/serialize.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 180,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-18T16:05:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s to make sure we always have a \"valid\" tile on disk. On my machine it takes ~1 min to write the tile. If I overwrote the target path directly I would not have a valid tile on disk for that period. \nit\u0027s essentially a transaction that is (almost) resistant to a crash. The only time I could lose my file, could happen if the program crashed between removing the old file and renaming the new file. That\u0027s a tiny risk and totally acceptable here.",
      "parentUuid": "cf1cd336_b82f6b64",
